  <thing id="rauSKrTent" name="Tentacles" description="The only part of a sand kraken that is normally exposed is its tentacles. For combat purposes, the creature&apos;s tentacles are treated as separate weapons. A single tentacle has an AC 20 (touch 14) and 15 hit points. Once a tentacle takes more than 15 hit points of damage, it is destroyed. A sand kraken can no longer use the destroyed tentacle to make attacks, however the loss of a tentacle cause the creature no other penalties. Furthermore, damage dealt to a tentacle does not count against the creature&apos;s total hit points. Lost tentacles regrow in 1d4 days." compset="RaceSpec">
