  <thing id="rauEDEyeRa" name="Eye Rays" description="Each of the creature&apos;s eyes stalks can produce a magical ray once per round as a free action. The creature can aim both of its eye rays in any direction. Each of its eye rays resembles a spell cast by a 12th-level caster and follows the rules for a ray (see Aiming a Spell in the Core Rulebook). Each eye ray has a range of 150 feet and a save DC of 17. The save DC is Constitution-based.\n\n{i}Hold Person{/i} Left eye-A target struck by this ray must succeed on a Will save or be affected as though by the spell. An eye of the deep will use this ray early in a fight so as to disable its opponents.\n\n{i}Hold Monster{/i} Right eye-A target struck by this ray must succeed on a Will save or be affected as though by the spell. This is used in the same manner as the hold person ray. Minor Image By combining the rays of both eyes, the eye of the deep can replicate the minor image spell. It does not have to succeed on an attack roll to use this ray. The illusion is generated at any point within range and in the eye of the deep&apos;s line of sight." compset="RaceSpec">
