  <thing id="ruBetGiaBr" name="Beetle, Giant Boring" description="Boring beetles feed primarily on wood, mold, fungus, and other organic matter. They make their lairs inside ancient tunnels and caverns, where they harvest and grow molds and fungi. Shriekers are prized for both food and their use as alarms to warn the boring beetles of intrusion. Boring beetles are about 9 feet long.\n\nBoring beetles bite with their powerful mandibles. Slain victims are dragged to their lair and used to grow new molds and fungi." compset="Race">
