  <thing id="ruBetGiaSl" name="Beetle, Giant Slicer" description="The slicer beetle closely resembles a large stag beetle and is often mistaken for such. However, the slicer beetle is more aggressive than the stag beetle. The creature dines on carrion, fresh meat, and leaves.\n\nStag beetles are about 10 feet long, but can grow to lengths of 20 feet or more.\n\nThe slicer beetle attacks by biting with its mandibles. A critical hit by the slicer beetle has a chance of severing a foe&apos;s arm or leg." compset="Race">
