  <thing id="rauBelAcdB" name="Acidic Blood" description="Each time a belabra is hit with a slashing or piercing weapon, all creatures within a 10-ft. radius must succeed on a DC 14 Reflex save or be sprayed by the creature&apos;s acidic blood. The save DC is Constitution-based.\n\nA creature that fails its save is partially blinded and overcome with fits of sneezing. Both effects last 1d6+2 rounds. An affected creature takes a -1 penalty to AC, loses its Dexterity bonus to AC (if any), moves at half speed, and takes a -2 penalty on Perception checks and on Strength- and Dexterity-based skills and checks. All checks relying on vision (such as reading and Perception) have a 50% chance of failing. All opponents are considered to have concealment (20% miss chance) relative to the blinded character." compset="RaceSpec">
