  <thing id="ruBoggart" name="Boggart" description="The boggart is a relative of the will-o&apos;-wisp. Sages believe it to be a sort of “larval” or immature form of said creature. It haunts many of the same places as its adult form and can be just as deadly when encountered. The typical boggart stands 2 feet tall.\n\nA boggart begins melee using its confusion ability. It then uses its electrical attack against its foes while changing forms as it wishes. Foes not in melee range are subjected to its electrical discharge attack (it fires a thin line of electricity from its hands). If reduced to 5 or less hit points, the boggart attempts to escape by changing to its will-o&apos;-wisp form and moving across grounds its enemies cannot traverse." compset="Race">
