  <thing id="ruCaterwau" name="Caterwaul" description="Caterwauls are semi-intelligent bipedal felines that possess great speed. They are natural predators and use their speed to stalk prey. The caterwaul&apos;s lair is most often a cave littered with sticks, twigs, and leaves, with walls covered in scratch marks where the beast has honed its claws.\n\nA caterwaul is about 6 feet long (or tall if on two legs). It weighs about 250 pounds.\n\nA caterwaul begins combat by utilizing its screech attack. After that, it uses its claw and bite attacks each round. By dropping to all fours, it can increase its movement speed." compset="Race">
