  <thing id="rauDvHsFBd" name="Fiery Body" description=" The oil coating a hellstoker&apos;s body is highly flammable. As such, a hellstoker hit with a fire effect bursts into flames. This deals no damage to the hellstoker, and deals 1d6 points of fire damage to any creature touching or grappling the hellstoker. The fire burns for 10 rounds before extinguishing. This does not damage the hellstoker&apos;s oily hide; therefore, it still retains its racial bonus to Escape Artist checks (see oily hide), and it can be caught on fire again." compset="RaceSpec">
