  <thing id="rauGallTCZ" name="Create Gallows Tree Zombie" description="When a creature dies within 15 feet of a gallows tree, it uses a sharpened tendril to slice open the creature&apos;s abdomen, thereby spilling the corpse&apos;s innards on the ground. The organs and fluids are then absorbed by the tree&apos;s roots. Corpses of a size other than Medium or Large are simply left to rot. Medium or Large corpses are filled with a greenish pollen fired from one of the tree&apos;s branches. The abdominal wound heals over the next 1d4 days, at which time the slain creature rises as a gallows tree zombie connected by a tether-vine to the gallows tree that created it. Gallows tree zombies possess none of their former abilities." compset="RaceSpec">
