  <thing id="ruGenHawan" name="Genie, Hawanar" description="Hawanar are the unlikely union of an efreeti noble and a djinni noble. Neither of the parent races truly accepts the hawanar but the djinn are more tolerant while the efreet usually execute or enslave hawanar offspring on sight, viewing them as something unnatural. A typical hawanar stands 12 feet tall and weighs about 1,100 pounds.\n\nHawanar society is ruled by a Rajah who is served by a multitude of beys, sheiks, sahibs, and sirdars The hawanar race has no true home and can be found spread throughout the planes (most dwell on the Plane of Air or a pocket plane of air and fire). Those that dwell on the Plane of Fire generally avoid the City of Brass and efreeti patrols due to the disdain the efreet have for them.\n\nHawanar wade into battle in a hail of fire and wind, relying on their spell-like abilities and holocone form to dissuade and vanquish its opponents. If combat goes against it, a hawanar assumes either gaseous form or holocone form and attempts to flee." compset="Race">
