  <thing id="ruGolBlood" name="Golem, Blood" description="Blood golems, contrary to their name, are not constructs: they are slugshaped clots of living blood, animated by some ancient ritual by a now unknown and unremembered spellcaster.\n\nA typical blood golem is 10 feet long and weighs 700 pounds.\n\nWhen living prey is detected, the blood golem rises up and appears as a slug-like headless humanoid. It attacks with its arms. When a blood golem reaches its maximum hit points for its Hit Dice, it splits into two identical golems.\n\nA blood golem&apos;s natural weapons are treated as magic weapons for the purpose of overcoming damage reduction." compset="Race">
