  <thing id="ruGolemRop" name="Golem, Rope" description=" Rope golems are constructed from many intertwined and knotted ropes and often serve as guardians to lesser nobles, wizards, clerics, and the like, protecting a treasure hoard or some ancient knowledge best kept hidden.\n\nThe typical rope golem stands 7 feet tall but weighs only about 100 pounds or so. Its long, gangly arms end in noose-like hands. A rope golem can expand its shape to fill a 10-foot area or contract its form to fill a space less than 2-1/2 feet square. Until it is activated, a rope golem appears to be nothing more than a pile of normal ropes. Rope golems cannot communicate.\n\nRope golems attack by rolling their ropey appendages into “fists” and pummeling a foe. If a rope golem hits, it attempts to slip its noose-like hands over its opponent&apos;s head and around its neck. If successful, a rope golem often maintains the hold until it is destroyed or its opponent is dead.\n\n{b}Construction{/b}\nA rope golem&apos;s body is spun and tied from 200 pounds of rope. Special bindings and powders worth 200 gp are used in the process.\n\n{b}CL{/b} 8th; {b}Price{/b} 14,200 gp\n{b}Requirements{/b} Craft Construct, animate rope, geas/quest, rope trick, creator must be caster level 8th; {b}Skill{/b} Craft (ropemaking) DC 13; {b}Cost{/b} 7,200" compset="Race">
