  <thing id="rauKhSunBt" name="Sundering Bite" description="A khargra can making a sunder attempt with its bite attack against an opponent&apos;s weapon or shield without provoking attacks of opportunity. Resolve this using the normal rules for a sunder attempt. If the khargra succeeds on its CMB roll, it deals 2d8+2 points of damage to the weapon or shield. Note, against a khargra, a weapon or shield&apos;s hardness is only one-half as effective as normal. This means that a light steel shield, for example, is considered to have a hardness of 5 rather than 10 against a khargra&apos;s sunder attack. A weapon or shield reduced to 0 or less hit points is destroyed and half of it is swallowed by the khargra.\n\nIt only uses this special attack against metal weapons and shields. Damaged armor and weapons gain the broken condition." compset="RaceSpec">
