  <thing id="ruMidnPedd" name="Midnight Peddler" description="The midnight peddler wanders city streets and is normally only encountered on fog-covered nights. He is first detected by the audible squeaking of the cart he pushes, the sound growing louder as he draws closer. The sound can be heard at a range of 300 feet with a successful DC 12 Perception check. The midnight peddler moves with a slow gait as he pushes his wooden cart. The contents of his cart vary each time he visits the Material Plane, but at any given time, he has available any item listed in the Pathfinder Roleplaying Game (see the Equipment section) with a value of 50 gp or less.\n\nThe midnight peddler shuns combat. If forced into battle, he uses his death chill ability at first opportunity and then plane shifts away." compset="Race">
