  <thing id="ruMuckdwel" name="Muckdweller" description="The muckdweller is a small, swamp-dwelling bipedal lizard that lives on a diet of carrion, fresh meat, plants, and insects. It has a long tail that allows it to swim rapidly through the water or maintain its balance when standing upright. Muckdwellers sometimes associate with lizardfolk.\n\nMuckdwellers stand about 4 feet tall. They speak their own language of croaks and hisses, and a rare few speak Draconic.\n\nThe muckdweller attacks by squirting muddy water at its foes. When it successfully blinds an opponent, it darts in and bites with its sharp teeth." compset="Race">
