  <thing id="ruObsidMin" name="Obsidian Minotaur" description="The obsidian minotaur is often employed by spellcasters as a guardian or killer and can be found performing such tasks. When employed as an assassin, the obsidian minotaur is quite effective, first striking fear into the heart of its opponent and then slaying it with no thought or consequence.\n\nAn obsidian minotaur stands 12 feet tall and weighs roughly 2,000 pounds.\n\nAs a guardian, the obsidian minotaur activates when trespassers enter an area it is programmed to protect. As an assassin, it actively hunts down the targeted victim. The creature attacks with its powerful claws, slashing and ripping its opponent&apos;s flesh. Against powerful foes, it employs its breath weapon.\n\n{b}Construction{/b}\nAn obsidian minotaur is sculpted from 2,500 pounds of black obsidian worth at least 3,000 gp.\n\n{b}CL{/b} 16th; {b}Price{/b} 53,000 gp\n{b}Requirements{/b} Craft Construct, burning hands, cat&apos;s grace, geas/quest, limited wish, creator must be caster level 16th; {b}Skill{/b} Craft (sculptures) DC 17 or Craft (masonry) DC 17; {b}Cost{/b} 28,000 gp" compset="Race">
