  <thing id="rauBlPDisg" name="Disgorge" description="A blood pudding that has infused itself with a host can force the creature&apos;s blood out through its pores, eyes, ears, and mouth. This is a standard action that deals 1d2 points of Constitution damage each round. At Constitution 0, the host dies and the blood pudding feeds on the corpse. When sated, the pudding exits, and to onlookers it appears as if the slain creature is bleeding profusely." compset="RaceSpec">
