  <thing id="rauAcdVulW" name="Vulnerability to Water" description="An acid creature erupts in a violent chemical reaction when touched by water. The creature takes 1d4 points of fire damage for each gallon of water poured into it. The reaction is so violent that all creatures within 5 ft. of the creature when the water hits it must succeed on a DC 15 Reflex save or take the same damage. Pouring water onto an acid subtype creature requires a successful ranged touch attack. Water from other sources, such as spells or effects that create water but do not specify an amount in gallons, deal 1d4 points of fire damage per caster level to an acid subtype creature within its area of effect. Damage from waterbased attacks, like the slam attack of a water elemental, is increased by 50% against an acid subtype creature. Note that this reaction does not occur when the acid subtype creature touches water, only when water touches the acid quasi-elemental." compset="RaceSpec">
