  <thing id="rauUbMultP" name="Multiple Personalities" description="The three heads of an ubue rarely get along with each other. Due to this division of personalities, there is a 15% chance in any given situation (usually once per encounter) that the heads get into an argument. An ubue engaged in an argument with itself takes a -2 circumstance penalty on attack rolls, Reflex saves, and to AC for the duration of the encounter, or until they can reach some sort of accord.\n\nIn a non-combat situation, an opponent can coerce an ubue into a self-argument by making a Charisma check opposed by the ubue&apos;s Wisdom check. If the ubue wins the opposed check, the character cannot attempt to coerce that ubue again for one day." compset="RaceSpec">
